    <note type="biography">
        <p>Explorer of Africa. Army officer in India, 1844–54. Explored Equatorial East Africa, 1855–63, and discovered Lake Victoria Nyanza, one of the sources of the Nile. Published <hi rend="italic">Journal of the discovery of the Nile</hi> in 1863. Awarded founders’ medal of the Royal Geographical Society, 1863.</p></note>
